result.execSummary:
The defendant Gregory Allan Behling was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Gregory Allan Behling is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Gregory Allan Behling was found guilty of Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Gregory Allan Behling in court with attorney Peter M Masana. Jordan Lippert appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Reading waived in Amended Complaint. Court went over the rights & elements. Defendant plead no contest to count 2, Court found defendant guilty, entered judgment, sentence: $1,083 fine on ct. 2, 60 days to pay fine or set up a payment plan with Clerk of Courts. Defendant may petition Court in writing, after one year, for expunction of record, contingent upon no new law violations and fine paid in full. Court granted 1 day jail credit. Ct. 1 dismissed. Stipulation filed in 14TR2511, no contest plea.
